article.description: — Jaylen Forbes had 22 points on 4-for-6 shooting from 3-point range and Tulane beat South Florida 76-57 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Forbes scores 22 to carry Tulane over South Florida 76-57
article.linkText: Forbes scores 22 to carry Tulane over South Florida 76-57
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- — Jaylen Forbes had 22 points on 4-for-6 shooting from 3-point range and Tulane beat South Florida 76-57 on Tuesday night. Kevin Cross had 19 points and eight rebounds for Tulane (12-11, 9-5 American Athletic Conference). Jadan Coleman added 16 points. Jalen Cook had 13 points and eight assists. Serrel Smith Jr. had 17 points for the Bulls (7-17, 2-10). Corey Walker Jr. added 11 points. Russel Tchewa had 9 points and 10 rebounds. The Green Wave improve to 2-0 against the Bulls this season. Tulane defeated South Florida 68-54 on Jan. 8. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
